What is the difference between length and length() method Give an Examples?
Ans.
A) length (Array Property):

length is a property of arrays in Java, and it represents the number of elements in the array. It is used to determine the size of an array.

int[] numbers = { 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 };
int arrayLength = numbers.length; // Accessing the length property of the array
System.out.println("Array Length: " + arrayLength); // Output: Array Length: 5

B) length() (String Method):

length() is a method provided by the String class in Java. It is used to find the number of characters in a string, including whitespace characters.

String text = "Hello, World!";
int stringLength = text.length(); // Calling the length() method on a String
System.out.println("String Length: " + stringLength); // Output: String Length: 13
